headline: 'Nobody Cares About Your Career' — McDonald's CEO Chris Kempczinski Says As He Warns Workers To Stop Expecting An 'Employment Deal' In Today's Market
summary: A blunt message about career responsibility is challenging long-held expectations between workers and employers. McDonald's (NYSE:MCD) CEO Chris Kempczinski recently shared a video on Instagram urging workers to rethink who is responsible for career progress and advancement, while warning that traditional "employment deals" no longer apply in today's labor market. He also acknowledged the advice might "hurt your feelings," framing it as practical guidance rather than criticism. Don't Miss: Misse

headline: Airbus Said to Beat 2025 Annual Delivery Goal of 790 Aircraft
summary: Airbus cut its previous 2025 guidance of about 820 handovers last month after a series of glitches involving its best-selling A320 model, including a massive recall for a software upgrade, followed by the discovery of fuselage panels on the same plane model that didn’t meet specifications and require extra inspections.  An Airbus spokesperson declined to comment on its annual deliveries, adding that audited orders and delivery figures will be published after markets close on Jan 12.  Aircraft deliveries at both Airbus and rival Boeing Co. are closely watched performance measures because they are the biggest source of cash and provide an indicator of supply network stability.
